00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:02,043
It was Frege in the 1800's who realized that doing

2
00:00:02,143 --> 00:00:04,915
mathematics involved manipulations of the following set of symbols:

3
00:00:05,015 --> 00:00:07,657
Constant symbols, such as numbers like 0, 1,

4
00:00:07,757 --> 00:00:10,087
e, or pi, or any other special element.

5
00:00:10,187 --> 00:00:12,830
Function symbols, such as addition or multiplication.

6
00:00:12,930 --> 00:00:16,409
Relation symbols, such as less than or in.

7
00:00:16,509 --> 00:00:20,223
Variables, quantifiers, brackets, and the Boolean connectives.

8
00:00:20,323 --> 00:00:22,432
The Boolean connectives can be represented

9
00:00:22,532 --> 00:00:24,063
by truth tables or logic gates.

10
00:00:24,163 --> 00:00:27,009
Importantly, in classical logic, a implies b

11
00:00:27,109 --> 00:00:28,817
is equivalent to not a or b

12
00:00:28,917 --> 00:00:30,358
and is given by this truth table.

13
00:00:30,458 --> 00:00:33,443
This is not the case in intuitionistic logic for example.

14
00:00:33,543 --> 00:00:36,095
But for now we stick to classical logic, and soon

15
00:00:36,195 --> 00:00:38,855
I will make a video on non-classical logics. So all

16
00:00:38,955 --> 00:00:41,669
of math comes down to manipulation of these symbols.

17
00:00:41,769 --> 00:00:45,994
We can divide these symbols into two groups, the logical and non-logical

18
00:00:46,094 --> 00:00:50,320
symbols. The logical symbols are common to all first order theories, and

19
00:00:50,420 --> 00:00:55,005
so proofs only involving the logical symbols apply to all possible structures.

20
00:00:55,105 --> 00:00:58,309
The non-logical symbols are specific to a given theory.

21
00:00:58,409 --> 00:01:00,922
For example if we are working with the theory of arithmetic,

22
00:01:01,022 --> 00:01:02,071
we would need the constant 0,

23
00:01:02,171 --> 00:01:02,985
the successor function,

24
00:01:04,085 --> 00:01:05,526
the addition or multiplication function,

25
00:01:06,626 --> 00:01:07,702
and perhaps the order relation.

26
00:01:07,802 --> 00:01:09,346
If we work with the theory of graphs,

27
00:01:09,446 --> 00:01:11,124
we only need a single binary relation E,

